<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-12-06T05:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-12-06T05:25:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/64: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">George</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                            Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-12-06T13:00:00+02:35">December 6, 1934—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>21. Anglo-Ethiopian Boundary Commission came as far as Italian
                                military post at Wal Wal water hole, Ogaden Desert, November 23rd
                                and was denied permission to proceed behind its lines although far
                                within Ethiopia. Italian reply to protest was tank and airplane
                                demonstration at Wal Wal yesterday. Commission has returned to Addis
                                Ababa but Ethiopian escort entrenched opposite Italian post which
                                has apparently been established there 3 years unknown to Ethiopian
                                Government. Situation regarded extremely grave here.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">George</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>